Matrics and their teachers are heading back to school today following a one week break. Spokesperson for the South African Democratic Teachers Union, Nomusa Cembi, says they'll be keeping a close eye on things. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Matrics and their teachers are heading back to school today following a one week break. Other grades are to be phased in in the following weeks. President Ramaphosa announced the break following demands from teacher unions and some parents for schools to be closed during the COVID-19 peak. WATCH: Ramaphosa addresses nation It was hoped that the extra time would be used to further improve safety measures amidst the pandemic. Spokesperson for the South African Democratic Teachers Union, Nomusa Cembi, says they'll be keeping a close eye on things. "We do hope the department has done all that we ask or requested of them so that the matriculants can start. It's a pity the department did not come back to us to tell us how far they are with being read," said Cembi. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. 